    {
      "id": "9905c604-821d-413e-af6b-c97dcb41cfdb",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "# Assuming you already have:\n# - df: your original dataframe with variables\n# - X_scaled: standardized predictors DataFrame\n# - model, res: your fitted OrderedModel and results\n# - predicted_categories: model predicted categories (from idxmax on predicted probs)\n# - categories: ordered categories list, e.g. ['Poor', 'Normal', 'Good']\n\n# 1. Identify threshold parameters in model parameters\nthresholds = ['Poor/Normal', 'Normal/Good']\n\n# 2. Extract only predictor names (exclude thresholds)\npredictor_names = [name for name in model.exog_names if name not in thresholds]\n\n# 3. Extract beta coefficients for predictors only\nbeta = res.params[predictor_names]\n\n# 4. Check alignment of columns and beta index\nassert all(X_scaled.columns == beta.index), \"Mismatch between X_scaled columns and beta index\"\n\n# 5. Compute latent variable (X_scaled @ beta)\nlatent_scores = X_scaled @ beta\n\n# 6. Extract threshold cutoffs\ncut1 = res.params['Poor/Normal']\ncut2 = res.params['Normal/Good']\n\n# 7. Assign categories manually based on latent scores and cutoffs\nmanual_pred = pd.cut(\n    latent_scores,\n    bins=[-np.inf, cut1, cut2, np.inf],\n    labels=categories,\n    ordered=True\n)\n\n# 8. Prepare comparison dataframe\ndf_with_predictions = df.copy()\ndf_with_predictions['Predicted_Economy_State_Model'] = predicted_categories\ndf_with_predictions['Predicted_Economy_State_Manual'] = manual_pred\n\n# Optional: Add scaled variables columns for reference\nfor col in X_scaled.columns:\n    df_with_predictions[f\"{col}_scaled\"] = X_scaled[col]\n\n# 9. (Optional) Check accuracy of manual vs model predictions\naccuracy = (predicted_categories == manual_pred).mean()\nprint(f\"Manual predictions match model predictions with accuracy: {accuracy:.4%}\")\n\n# 10. View the first few rows\nprint(df_with_predictions.head(10))",
